### Feature 1: Free-Text RAG Input + 3-Chat Limiter

After the 7-step button flow completes, unlock a text input box that hits the RAG API (`POST /api/v1/chat`). After 3 free-text questions, auto-trigger the Calendly appointment CTA.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Projects/DHUMI%20Projects/US%20insurance%20chatbot/demo/index.html)

**Changes:**
- Add `let freeTextCount = 0;` to STATE section
- Add new `showRAGInput()` function that renders a persistent text input
- In [endSession()](file:///c:/Projects/DHUMI%20Projects/US%20insurance%20chatbot/demo/index.html#659-671), call `showRAGInput()` instead of ending the conversation
- `showRAGInput` sends the user's question to `http://localhost:8000/api/v1/chat` via `fetch()`
- Each successful RAG response increments `freeTextCount`
- When `freeTextCount === 3`, disable the text input and inject the appointment CTA with inline Calendly popup
- Add CSS for `.rag-input-bar` (sticky bottom input)

