### Feature 3: Cloudflare Turnstile CAPTCHA on Lead Capture

Protect the lead form and Calendly link from spam bots using Cloudflare Turnstile (free, privacy-friendly, invisible CAPTCHA).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Cloudflare Turnstile requires a **site key**. For MVP/demo purposes, we will use Cloudflare's public test keys:
> - Site key: `1x00000000000000000000AA` (always passes)
> - Production keys must be obtained from the Cloudflare dashboard before deployment.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Projects/DHUMI%20Projects/US%20insurance%20chatbot/demo/index.html)

**Changes:**
- Add `<script src="https://challenges.cloudflare.com/turnstile/v0/api.js" async defer></script>` to `<head>`
- In [addLeadForm()](file:///c:/Projects/DHUMI%20Projects/US%20insurance%20chatbot/demo/index.html#312-336), insert a `<div class="cf-turnstile" data-sitekey="..." data-callback="onCaptchaPass"></div>` widget inside the form
- The submit button is initially disabled; it enables only after `onCaptchaPass()` is called
- [submitLead()](file:///c:/Projects/DHUMI%20Projects/US%20insurance%20chatbot/demo/index.html#465-541) reads the Turnstile token from `document.querySelector('[name="cf-turnstile-response"]').value`
- In a production deployment, the FastAPI backend would verify this token server-side via the Turnstile `/siteverify` endpoint

